      <TEXTAREA NAME="body" ROWS="15"
        COLS="50" WRAP="virtual">>Hi there, 
>first of all, once you attack something, 
>it can see you everywhere in 
>the zone. Invis will not stop 
>that. Personally I think this is 
>BS....but.... 
>Feign Death is complicated ! Here are 
>some things you have to remember: 
>
>1. Dont feign death while you have 
>a pet. They will keep hitting 
>you. 
>2. If you get the message "...has 
>fallen to the ground", your attempt 
>has failed! Get up and cast 
>again...if you can. Make a hotkey 
>for STAND. 
>3. Feign Death is a spell not 
>a skill (lucky monks)...it can and 
>will be interrupted. 
>4. Feign Death will not work until 
>you stop attacking the opponent. Switch 
>off melee! 
>5. It will not work when you 
>have casted DoT on the opponent. 
>
>6. When you have feigned successfully...and the 
>opponent has left the area...get up 
>and GATE! They will come back 
>for you ASAP. 
>7. When you play with a group 
>inside a dungeon, they usually DONT 
>want you to make a pet 
>(to avoid the pet trains). DoT 
>is bugged in dungeons...you will not 
>get EXP if the opponent dies 
>to DoT there. So you will 
>use DD spells a lot. This 
>is the situation where Feign Death 
>comes in handy...... 
>Conclusion: Feign Death will almost NEVER work! 
>Get JBoots and use Harmshield....much more 
>effective (especially in Unrest). On the 
>other side, Feign Death ..as crappy 
>as it is....has saved my life 
>many times. I dont want to 
>miss it..... 
>Good luck, Neric Soulstalker (27th lvl Xegony) 
>
</TEXTAREA>
     
